HEADWORD: Credendum
<hw>Cre*den"dum</hw> <pr>(kr?-d?n"d?m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Credenda</plw> <pr>(-d<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.,
fr. <ets>credere</ets> to believe.]</ety> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>A
thing to be believed; an article of faith; -- distinguished from
